postcontent: I have a Daisy VL 22 plus 800 +/- rounds of caseless ammo.  If  you dont know the history of this gun, it is facinating.  The gun actually uses air to ignite a charge that is connected to a .22 caliber lead slug.  The charge is just attached, no case or brass, and no primer.  The air being compressed (like in a diesel cylinder) creates the heat necessary to ingite the charge.  This is the standard model, of which about 19,000 were made, but few survive.  I will only sell as a package, gun and ammo as one unit.  Shoots great and functions as it should.If the ad is still up, it is still for sale.I dont have an actual picture of the gun right here at work but have attached one from google.  Mine is identical.I am between Nashville and Rocky Mount
